{"key":"processedPost-9521139","value":{"id":9521139,"first":9513819,"last":9524923,"when":1230702257,"utime":"12/31/08 07:44 AM","content":"The reason they get on the tops of the caps is aerodynamics.&nbsp; The spores are shaped similar to an airplane wing and ejected from the basidia with extreme force.&nbsp; The actually do a 180 and then often settle on the tops of the caps.&nbsp; Next time, harvest sooner.&nbsp; Your mushrooms will be of higher quality and taste much better.&nbsp; I like to pick them before the veil tears and the cap has even opened yet.&nbsp; This is the stage they're at their best, just like the button mushrooms you get in the grocery store.<br />RR","title":"Re: Help purpleish (maybe deadly?) mold","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}